Another Reſolution was by divers of the Judges;
10 Apr. 9 Car. 1. at the Seſſions at Newgate.
                   That the King may pardon an Indictment upon the Statute of 5 Eliz. and that he may by the Common Law give a Licenſe to one to exerciſe a Trade, for all his Life-time, although he had not been an Apprentice to it, becauſe it is not malum in ſe, but malum prohibitum.

It is a good and pleaſant thing to dwell together in Ʋnity;
                  Pſal. 133.1. Eph. 4.3.13. and we muſt endeavour to keep the 
                     Ʋnity of the Spirit in the Bond of Peace, which ſurely is moſt broken by Perſecution.
